    {
      "thumb": "https://cdn.bsky.app/img/feed_thumbnail/plain/did:plc:zymiavmtif2rj5oklzyzslpu/bafkreicblz6susbx5o4m2f2zdgqtotaodmxetqembiud7wyujd2mjvbfrq",
      "fullsize": "https://cdn.bsky.app/img/feed_fullsize/plain/did:plc:zymiavmtif2rj5oklzyzslpu/bafkreicblz6susbx5o4m2f2zdgqtotaodmxetqembiud7wyujd2mjvbfrq",
      "alt": "The imagination, filler of the void, is essentially a liar. It does away with the third dimension, for only real objects have three dimensions. It does away with multiple relation-ships.\nTo try to define the things which, while they do indeed happen, yet remain in a sense imaginary. War. Crimes. Acts of revenge. Extreme affliction.\n62\nIMAGINATION WHICH FILLS THE VOID\nThe crimes in Spain were actually perpetrated and yet they resembled mere acts of boastfulness.\nRealities which have no more dimensions than a dream.\nIn the case of evil, as in that of dreams, there are not multiple readings.* Hence the simplicity of criminals.\nCrimes flat like dreams on both sides: on the side of the executioner and on the side of the victim. What is more frightful than to die in a nightmare?\nGRAVITY AND GRACE\ners, slaves, prostitutes, and pass through no matter what suffering without being purified.\nWe must continually suspend the work of the imagination in filling the void within ourselves.\nIf we accept no matter what void, what stroke of fate can prevent us from loving the universe?\nWe have the assurance that, come what may, the universe is full.",
